Package: ouladFormat
Type: Package
Title: Loads and Formats the Open University Learning Analytics Dataset for Data Analysis
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Emma", "Howard", email = "emhoward@tcd.ie", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8104-1351"))
Description: The Open University Learning Analytics Dataset (oulad), available from
    Kuzilek et al. (2017) <doi:10.1038/sdata.2017.171>, 
    contains information across 22 presentations of 7 Open University modules, and from
    the 32,593 students (or 28,785 unique students) taking these modules in 2013 and 
    2014. The ouladFormat package loads, cleans and formats the oulad for data analysis 
    with its functions returning formatted data sets (each row of the dataset is an 
    individual student). The package’s main function, combined_dataset, allows 
    the user to choose whether the returned dataset includes assessment, demographics, 
    virtual learning environment (VLE), or registration variables. The user can 
    also choose whether the VLE variables should be daily counts, weekly counts, 
    counts of activities, in binary format, normalised etc.
